Create Document

To create Document:

1. Click the Create / Upload button or when in the Cultural Objects click on the Create Document button

Have in mind that if the second option is used the next two points will be preset and can't be changed

 

2. Select the context you want the Document to be created

Every object exists in the context of other objects. If there is no other object related to the current, it exists at least in the context of the user who created it. You can create the Document in the context of a cultural object or in the context of project or any folder. Creating Document in the context of another system objects means that this Document will be part of that context and the permissions on that Document will depend on this context.

 

3. Select "Document" from the drop-down with types.

To find easily the Document in the list with system objects that can be created you can start to type directly in the field. The list with types is filtered as you write in the field.

4. Select the Document Sub Type you want to be created. In the example below is selected Condition Report

To find easily the Document sub type in the list with system objects that can be created you can start to type directly in the field. The list with types is filtered as you write in the field.

5. Fill mandatory Document data

The mandatory data depends on the type of the document you want to be created. Following fields can appear as mandatory depending on the selected type.

 

6. Press Create

The document will be opened in Edit mode.
